## 2. **WebSocket Servers com NDJSON**

### Recursos para Node.js/Bun 2026

#### Guias Técnicos
- **[Bun WebSocket Guide](https://bun.com/docs/guides/websocket/simple)** - Implementação nativa de WebSocket
- **[NDJSON Specification](https://github.com/ndjson/ndjson-spec)** - Especificação oficial
- **[NDJSON NPM Package](https://www.npmjs.com/package/ndjson)** - Parse de NDJSON streaming
- **[OneUptime: WebSocket Reconnection Logic](https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-01-16-duplicate-requests-in-websocket-connections)** - Janeiro 2026

#### Exemplos de Código

#### Servidor WebSocket com NDJSON (Bun)
```javascript
import { Bun } from 'bun'

const server = Bun.serve({
  port: 3000,
  websocket: {
    open(ws) {
      ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'connected', correlationId: generateId() }))
    },
    message(ws, message) {
      try {
        // Parse NDJSON (newline-delimited)
        const lines = message.toString().split('\n')
        for (const line of lines) {
          if (line.trim()) {
            const data = JSON.parse(line)
            handleNDJSONMessage(ws, data)
          }
        }
      } catch (error) {
        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ error: 'Invalid NDJSON' }))
      }
    },
    close(ws, code, reason) {
      console.log('WebSocket closed:', code, reason.toString())
    }
  }
})

function handleNDJSONMessage(ws, data) {
  if (data.type === 'request') {
    // Responder com correlationId
    const response = {
      type: 'response',
      correlationId: data.correlationId,
      data: { result: 'processed' }
    }
    ws.send(JSON.stringify(response))
  }
}
```

#### Client com Exponential Backoff (Node.js)
```javascript
class NDJSONWebSocket {
  constructor(url) {
    this.url = url
    this.reconnectDelay = 1000
    this.maxDelay = 30000
    this.requests = new Map()
    this.socket = null
  }

  connect() {
    this.socket = new WebSocket(this.url, [], {
      headers: { 'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}` }
    })

    this.socket.onopen = () => {
      console.log('Connected')
      this.reconnectDelay = 1000
    }

    this.socket.onmessage = (event) => {
      const data = JSON.parse(event.data)
      if (data.correlationId && this.requests.has(data.correlationId)) {
        const { resolve, reject } = this.requests.get(data.correlationId)
        this.requests.delete(data.correlationId)
        resolve(data)
      }
    }

    this.socket.onclose = () => {
      this.reconnect()
    }
  }

  reconnect() {
    setTimeout(() => {
      this.connect()
      this.reconnectDelay = Math.min(this.reconnectDelay * 2, this.maxDelay)
    }, this.reconnectDelay)
  }

  async request(data) {
    const correlationId = generateId()
    const promise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
      this.requests.set(correlationId, { resolve, reject })
    })

    this.socket.send(JSON.stringify({ ...data, correlationId }))

    // Timeout de 30s
    const timeout = setTimeout(() => {
      if (this.requests.has(correlationId)) {
        this.requests.delete(correlationId)
        reject(new Error('Request timeout'))
      }
    }, 30000)

    return promise.finally(() => clearTimeout(timeout))
  }
}
```

## 3. **Protocolos Request/Response sobre WebSocket**

### Padrões de Correlation

#### Basic Request/Response Pattern
```javascript
// Request
const requestId = nanoid()
const request = {
  correlationId: requestId,
  type: 'request',
  data: { action: 'getUser', userId: '123' }
}

// Response
const response = {
  correlationId: requestId,  // Mantém o mesmo ID
  type: 'response',
  data: { user: { id: '123', name: 'John' } }
}
```

#### Promise-based Implementation
```javascript
class RequestResponseManager {
  constructor(ws) {
    this.ws = ws
    this.pendingRequests = new Map()
    this.requestId = 0
  }

  async sendRequest(message) {
    const correlationId = ++this.requestId
    const promise = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
      const timeout = setTimeout(() => {
        this.pendingRequests.delete(correlationId)
        reject(new Error('Timeout'))
      }, 5000)

      this.pendingRequests.set(correlationId, { resolve, reject, timeout })
    })

    this.ws.send(JSON.stringify({
      ...message,
      correlationId,
      type: 'request'
    }))

    return promise
  }

  handleMessage(message) {
    if (message.correlationId && this.pendingRequests.has(message.correlationId)) {
      const { resolve, reject, timeout } = this.pendingRequests.get(message.correlationId)
      clearTimeout(timeout)
      this.pendingRequests.delete(message.correlationId)

      if (message.error) {
        reject(new Error(message.error))
      } else {
        resolve(message.data)
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Autenticação Bearer Token

#### Client-Side (Node.js/Bun)
```javascript
const token = "your-jwt-token"

const socket = new WebSocket('wss://api.example.com/ws', null, {
  headers: {
    'Authorization': `Bearer ${token}`,
    'Content-Type': 'application/x-ndjson'
  }
})

socket.onopen = () => {
  // Enviar primeira mensagem autenticada
  socket.send(JSON.stringify({
    correlationId: generateId(),
    type: 'authenticate',
    token: token
  }))
}
```

#### Server-Side (ElysiaJS)
```javascript
import { Elysia } from 'elysia'
import { jwt } from '@elysiajs/jwt'

const app = new Elysia()
  .use(jwt({
    secret: process.env.JWT_SECRET
  }))
  .ws('/ws', {
    async beforeHandle({ jwt, headers, set }) {
      const authHeader = headers.get('Authorization')
      if (!authHeader?.startsWith('Bearer ')) {
        set.status = 401
        return { error: 'Missing token' }
      }

      try {
        const token = authHeader.substring(7)
        return await jwt.verify(token)
      } catch {
        set.status = 401
        return { error: 'Invalid token' }
      }
    },

    message({ user, message, broadcast }) {
      // Processar mensagem NDJSON
      const data = JSON.parse(message)

      if (data.type === 'request') {
        const response = {
          correlationId: data.correlationId,
          type: 'response',
          data: { user: user.id }
        }
        return JSON.stringify(response)
      }
    }
  })
```

## Resumo dos Padrões Encontrados

1. **LiveKit Agents**: Uso de `@function_tool` decorator com async/await, suporte para multi-agentes e integração com múltiplos provedores AI (Deepgram, Gemini, Cartesia)

2. **WebSocket NDJSON**: Processamento linha por linha com split('\n'), estrutura JSON com correlationId para request/response

3. **Reconnection**: Exponential backoff com random jitter, manuseio de estado e fila de mensagens

4. **Autenticação**: Bearer token no header durante WebSocket handshake, verificação JWT no servidor

5. **Correlation**: UUIDs ou IDs sequenciais para correlacionar request/response, timeout handling e promise-based patterns

Esses padrões são amplamente utilizados em produção em 2026, especialmente com o ecossistema Bun gaining traction para aplicações de alta performance.
